node.text: No rain delays in Newfoundland - "The Main River is truly unspoiled in every sense and hands down one of the most amazing places to fly fish for Atlantic Salmon in the world. Our base camp was set back from the river so every morning we’d hike down into the valley through the many bogs keeping an eye out for moose and bear as the morning fog hung low in the trees. We shared some amazing experiences, great fishing, shore lunches, and the occasional cheeky river side whiskey." - Photographer @scottysherin ⁠
